Job Description


Ubisoft IT is looking for a Virtualization Administrator to join the Enterprise Infrastructure Operation team in Montreal as part of the Ubisoft IT group. The team is responsible for the corporate infrastructure and provides services for all teams within Ubisoft.

As a Virtualization Administrator, you’ll be responsible for the health and operations of our global virtualization infrastructure. You’ll also be responsible for automating and improving the technical solutions to deliver the most reliable and performant service.


Responsibilities



Improve service observability by developing monitoring and alerting;

Improve service management by measuring and improving service metrics;

Simplify deployment and operations by automating tasks;

Develop a critical eye on the infrastructure to improve it with creative solutions;

Maintain proactively clusters for optimal performance, ensuring scalability and stability;

Secure implementation of technical standards with configuration management tools;

Ensure to date documentation and efficient communication;

Ensure communication with 3rd parties and vendors when escalation is required;

Respond to user and departmental requests to solve complex technical issues;

Be Available to rotate schedule for emergencies.




Qualifications



Good experience in virtualization administration of vSphere and vCenter applied to medium or large infrastructure with multiple sites and experience with vSAN is a plus;

Experience with scripting languages such as Python, PowerShell and Bash;

Experience with automation tools and principles, CICD pipeline, API, Ansible and Gitlab;

Knowledge of Linux OS administration;

Knowledge of monitoring tools such as Prometheus, Grafana and ELK;

Knowledge of containers such as Docker or Kubernetes.




