Canadian Bank Note Company designs, launches, and supports secure solutions for currency and excise, border security, identification and lottery systems for countries around the world. Our operations in Sault Ste. Marie focus on our lottery and charitable gaming operations that turn paper-based charitable games into profitable, popular digital properties. Located in professional sports venues and community gaming centres, we offer an enhanced, secure and fun way for fans to participate and support local good causes like children’s hospitals, amateur athletics and educational initiatives.





What’s In It For You?





This is a perfect opportunity for a recent graduate who is looking to build their IT career in an enterprise level environment. You’ll be surrounded by a team that is there to support your growth every step of the way, and they’ll provide the training, coaching and mentoring that will ensure your success. As your skillset and confidence develop, you can look forward to leading projects that will grow in scope, further developing your skills through hands-on experience in an environment that constantly embraces new technology.





What Will You Do?





As a member of the Infrastructure &amp; Applications team you will help design, build, deploy, monitor, and maintain our enterprise class IT systems. More specifically, you will:


Set-up and maintain enterprise hardware such as servers, storage systems, firewalls, switches, routers and workstations;

Set-up and maintain enterprise software such as operating systems, hypervisors, systems managements solutions and malware protection;

Monitor and support production and test lab environments;

Develop shell scripts to automate repetitive tasks;

Provide support at trade shows and demonstrations.






What Will Help You Succeed?





A diploma or degree in Computer Science/Engineering or related discipline and 0-3 years of relevant experience will position you for success in this role, but it is not an absolute requirement so long as you possess the following:






Technical Knowledge







Solid understanding of computer hardware and software terminology and concepts;

Understanding of and/or experience with operating systems such as Windows and Linux.;

Understanding of and/or experience with virtualization technologies (e.g. ESX);

Understanding of and/or experience with DBMS (e.g. SQL Server, Postgress, MongoDB);

Understanding of and/or experience with scripting and task automation;

Understanding of and/or experience with Networking (e.g. firewalls, routers, switches, VLANs, TCP/IP).

Understanding of and/or experience with Cloud Computing concepts (e.g. Microsoft Azure, AWS)







Soft Skills







An analytical mind with proven troubleshooting and problem-solving skills;

Excellent time management skills – organization, prioritization in particular;

Well developed interpersonal and communication skills.






Mandatory Requirements



The ability to participate in an on-call rotation;

Ability to travel to customer sites;

Enthusiasm!





People who enjoy variety and think beyond their job descriptions succeed here. As part of the team at CBN, you job is to take your career in new directions and be part of our customer’s success stories. So, if you’re looking for the chance to work for a global technology company, explore new opportunities, and deliver exceptional work to your customers, we want to hear from you!




As an Equal Opportunity Employer, Canadian Bank Note Company, Limited is committed to achieving a skilled and diversified workforce that reflects the diversity of the Canadian population. We encourage applications from women, visible minorities, people with disabilities and Aboriginal people. Canadian Bank Note Company Limited is committed to developing inclusive, barrier-free selection processes and work environments. If contacted regarding this competition, please advise the interview coordinator of any accommodation measures you may require.

