Job Description


Our infrastructure teams of 25 people from Montreal, Paris and Singapore are all part the Ubisoft DevOps journey. As part of this team, you will help develop, design and create our on premise cloud infrastructure currently hosted on Openstack. Adding your knowledge of storage, internal operating systems, scaleability, and reliability will help the team thrive to success.


Responsibilities



Work with your team to invent, design, and build Cloud systems that are stable, performant and maintainable;

Support the services in production by managing alerts, solving issues and applying best practices;

Identify patterns that affect the reliability of a product and replace them with automation or other technical innovation;

Improve continuous integration and delivery systems, as well as CI/CD pipelines;

Work on projects with internal customers, stakeholders, and peers to improve our systems and processes;

Read, write, and debug code in order to understand, implement, and operate a complete system.



(On Call rotation between teammate, during local business hours, once a month)


Qualifications



Experience on OpenStack or deep knowledge of GNU/Linux systems;

Experience with DevOps, CI/CD, scripting and orchestration/automation tools;

Experience with monitoring tools such as Sensu, Zabbix, or Prometheus is an asset;

Experience with Container technology such as Kubernetes, or Docker is an asset;

